{"type":"message","id":"0f25d7e7","parentId":"56bd62fc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:19:59.090Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xhu1ql9142zr_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 111915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI analysis done - found 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7) - true causal anchors\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\n1. I could create a new script to perform the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n2. I could modify pulse.ps1 to incorporate CFI weighting\r\n3. I could create documentation for the experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven that the pending task is \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\", I should design and implement this experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a script that:\r\n1. Takes the frequency invariants from the research data\r\n2. Computes CFI weights\r\n3. Compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-only prediction accuracy\r\n4. Outputs results\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the CFI_RESULTS.md, it has the data I need. Let me check what data is available.\r\n\r\nThe document mentions:\r\n- 44.8% of invariants have CFI=0\r\n- 5.7% have CFI>=0.7\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nFor a proper experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Get actual invariant data with both frequency and CFI values\r\n2. Create a comparison script\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's raw data available. Looking at the goals, I see references to `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`. I should look at this file to understand the data structure.\r\n\r\nSince I don't have the actual file content visible to me, let me create a Python script that can:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll design a flexible script to compare compression methods, focusing on extracting key metrics like CFI scores, frequency data, and prediction accuracy. The script will generate synthetic data if no raw data exists, ensuring I can test the experiment's core logic. By using command-line arguments, I'll make the script adaptable to different data sources and experimental requirements.\r\n\r\nThe key steps will involve:\r\n- Parsing command-line inputs for data source\r\n- Generating synthetic data as a fallback\r\n- Calculating compression weights\r\n- Comparing prediction accuracy between methods\r\n- Generating a results file for further analysis\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The next pending action is to run a CFI-weighted compression experiment comparing it against the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This script will compare CFI-weighted invariants vs frequency-only invariants for next-pulse prediction, testing the hypothesis that CFI weighting preserves more causal signal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\nCompares CFI-weighted invariants vs frequency-only invariants for prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\nHypothesis: CFI weighting (filtering noise, boosting causal anchors) should\r\noutperform frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport random\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef load_cfi_data():\r\n    \"\"\"Load CFI results from research document.\"\"\"\r\n    cfi_results_path = Path(\"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\")\r\n    if not cfi_results_path.exists():\r\n        return generate_synthetic_data()\r\n    \r\n    # Parse CFI_RESULTS.md for invariant data\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    try:\r\n        with open(cfi_results_path) as f:\r\n            content = f.read()\r\n            # Extract data table if present\r\n            lines = content.split('\\n')\r\n            for line in lines:\r\n                if '|' in line and not line.strip().startswith('|---'):\r\n                    parts = [p.strip() for p in line.split('|') if p.strip()]\r\n                    if len(parts) >= 3 and parts[0].replace('.','').isdigit():\r\n                        idx, freq, cfi = parts[0], float(parts[1]), float(parts[2])\r\n                        invariants.append({'index': idx, 'frequency': freq, 'cfi': cfi})\r\n    except Exception:\r\n        pass\r\n    \r\n    if not invariants:\r\n        return generate_synthetic_data()\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef generate_synthetic_data():\r\n    \"\"\"Generate synthetic invariants matching CFI_RESULTS.md statistics.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"[EXPERIMENT] Using synthetic data matching CFI_RESULTS.md statistics\")\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    for i in range(1000):\r\n        rand = random.random()\r\n        if rand < 0.448:\r\n            cfi = 0.0  # 44.8% pure noise\r\n        elif rand < 0.942:\r\n            cfi = random.uniform(0.0, 0.7)  # 49.4% low CFI\r\n        else:\r\n            cfi = random.uniform(0.7, 1.0)  # 5.8% high CFI (causal anchors)\r\n        \r\n        freq = random.randint(1, 60)\r\n        invariants.append({'index': i, 'frequency': freq, 'cfi': cfi})\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef compute_frequency_weights(invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Baseline: weight by frequency only.\"\"\"\r\n    max_freq = max(inv['frequency'] for inv in invariants)\r\n    return {inv['index']: inv['frequency'] / max_freq for inv in invariants}\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi_weights(invariants, cfi_threshold=0\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:19:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365599088}}
